<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
<head>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0">
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/directory/site.css">
</head>

<script src="/common/loadNav.js"> </script>


<body>
	<div id="navbar">
	</div>

	<h1>Automatically Welcome New Users</h1>

	<div id="confirmRestore">
		<p>The directory can automatically send a "Welcome to the Directory" email to new users whenever they are added.  Alternately, you
		   can manually send out emails at one time to all members who have not yet signed into the directory.  Most of the time
		   you will probably want this feature enabled.  However, when setting up the directory for the first time, you might wish to turn
		   off this feature until all the entries have been added (so that the first people to view the directory don't see a nearly
		   empty directory.</p>
		<p>This feature can be turned on or off at any time.</p>
		<br>
		<form action = "/directory/autoWelcome" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
			<center>
			<input type="checkbox" id="autoWelcome" name="autoWelcome" <%= ($autoWelcome) ? 'checked' : '' %> />
			<label for="autoWelcome">Send automatic welcome email.</label>
			<br><br>
			<button id="sendBackup" type="submit">Save Change</button>
			</center
		</form>
	</div>
</body>

</html>
